# choreChart

Simple API to select chores for the sullivan fam.

## Chores Collection [/chores]

### List All Chores [GET]

List all chores that are available.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        [
            {
                "name": "table",
                "id":1
            },{
                "name": "counters",
                "id": 2
            },{
                "name":"floor",
                "id": 3
            },{
                "name":"pots",
                "id": 4
            },{
                "name":"shoes"
                "id": 5
            }
        ]

## Chores Detail [/chores/{name}]

Use the Chores Detail resource to get the chore detail

+ Parameters

    + name (required, string, `pots`) ... Name of the chore

### List Chore Details [GET]

Use this to find out who is on what chore for today
+ Response 200 (application/json)

           {
                "Chore":"Pots"
                "day": "Monday",
                "Worker": "John"
            }


## Day Detail [/chores/{name}/day/{day}]
+ Parameters
    + name (required, string, `Counters`) ... Name of the chore
    + day (required, string, `Monday`) ... Day of the week
    

### List Chores for the Day [GET]

Use this to list out all the chores and their worker for a given day.
If no day is given, then list for today. 

+ Response 200 (application/json)

           {
                "Chore":"Counters"
                "day": "Monday"
                "Worker": "John"
            }
            
            


### Create a New Chore [POST]

You may create your own chore chart using this action. It takes a JSON
object containing chores and their relevant workers.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "chore": "Back Yard",
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /chores/{id}

    + Body

            {
                "name":"Back Yard"
                "id": 6
            }

## Workers Collection [/workers]

### List all Workers [GET]

List all available workers.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

